= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =
configset  GLOBAL  confirm_url = [VALUE]
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value : [defined during installation]
Data Type     : string
Variable Group: access, token
Password Notes: Visible only with password. Set with global password. 
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset GLOBAL confirm_url = no server configured


The URL that is used to return confirmation tokens.  The only purpose
of this variable is to supply a value to be used in the confirmation
messages that are sent out.  The embedded variable $TOKEN will be
expanded to the token being confirmed.

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
